<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee27dfae-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s328"><num value="328">§ 328.</num><heading> Power to amend, repeal, etc., reserved</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Congress may at any time amend, suspend, or repeal any or all of the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idee27dfaf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1890-08-30/ch841/s6">Aug. 30, 1890, ch. 841, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/26/419">26 Stat. 419</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
